lyricText:
I've got no business praying
I'm finished being good
Now I can finally be okay
And not the way I thought I should, mm

All those empty rooms
We could have been anywhere, anywhere else
Instead, I made a bed with apathy

Isn't like I did it on purpose
I just forget the second I learned it
In another life, we were arsonists

And, baby, it came true
All the little things that I wished for
That I never said out loud
Out of my mouth

Trying to find a reason to fight
But someone's got my head in a ziptie

You don't open your eyes for a while
You just breathe that moment down.

And on that very same day
She'd join a kind of relay
I'd pass her the baton and
I'd say you better run

'Cause this thing has been going
For many generations
But there is so much healing
That still needs to be done
